description: Serves as Electronic Warfare Test Engineer and Analyst within the 28th Test and Evaluation Squadron, Electronic Warfare Division for the purpose of leading the government assessment and evaluation of electronic warfare systems. Technical expert responsible for testing the capabilities of the Combat Air Forces (CAF) operational requirements for the functional employment of electronic warfare systems to include related hardware and software for A-10, B-2, B-52, F-15, F-16, C-130 and HH-60. Improves the combat capability, reliability. and lethality of Air Force electronic warfare systems through operationally realistic testing. Plans, conducts, and reports on force development evaluation (FDE) of operational fighter and bomber electronic warfare, and weapons systems. Evaluates electronic attack (EA) and electronic protection (EP) systems, techniques, and applications. Provides input and assistance to Department of Defense (DoD), USAF, ACC, USA, Air Force Operational Test and Evaluation Center (AFOTEC), and Air Force Materiel Command (AFMC) customers in the development of test plans. conduct of test projects. collection of test data, and production of final reports on both developmental T&E (DT&E) and operational T&E (OT&E) programs as directed by HQ ACC. Provides operational support/expertise to USA test engineers for planning, executing and reporting of radar and missile systems testing.

description: Served as an intelligence analyst and radar expert for several foreign surface-to-air missile (SAM) systems. Analyzed and evaluated all-source data and intelligence data (ELINT, IMINT, COMINT, SIGINT) to ensure that US weapons and countermeasures, war plans and tactics incorporated the most accurate threat assessments. Responsible for periodic EWIR updates for several threat systems. Coordinated, conducted, and attended conferences, briefings, and tests in support of foreign material exploitation and live fire exercises, flight tests, and ground tests at Nellis AFB and Eglin AFB test ranges.
